Reply  Re: Where have all the heros gone 8-(<br>
-------------------------------------------<br>
 Irontaail, I feel you have brought up a significant part of the 'other' side of EQ. Apparently for some of the players, the roleplaying aspect is more on ridding the environs of Norrath of gods and such, and in turn attempting to be near god-like themselves. The 'other' side of this roleplaying is to be a part of Norrath, concerned with the fates of others destined to wander through the perils.<br>
<br>
As a member of a small guild, we only have a handful of post 50 players, I have taken to accept the role of honor and helping others. Do we do planar raids? Of course not, we are not that large of a guild. Will we do them someday? Maybe not. But then we are not looking to become a guild solely revolving about the 'best' raids. We strive more to be a family, quaint as that may seem.<br>
<br>
Would the guild drop even one of our small raids to come to zone after being asked to rid the zone of a pesky giant or griffon? Most likely we would, particularly if we felt there was not going to be relief for that zone by a passing Uber. Would we search a zone to aid another to find a corpse, having no necro? Yes, we've done that too.<br>
<br>
Shortly after I joined this guild I was a mighty cleric around level 25 when a much younger person asked if I would be willing to help them get their body from inside Qeynos Aquaducts. Full of foolishness, I agrees, as what possible dangers could there be in a lowbie zone like the Aquaducts?<br>
<br>
On that day I learned the feeling of utter dispair as I sat naked at the gates of Qeynos, having no idea where I left my corpse, or even what killed me. All was lost, months of work as a soloing cleric who seldom found the same people on enough to readily form groups. Before I knew it several of my new guildmates, remember the highest was maybe 35 at the time and most were just over me in levels or even younger. Four determined young Knights entered the Aquaducts, died several gruesome deaths with no possibilty of rezzing, intent in recovering not only my corpse, but that other young person's corpse. I felt on that day my greatest gratitude.<br>
<br>
Since that day I have taken to give back to the citizens of Norrath in whatever slight payback this would mean. I have now often saw a younger citizen at their lowest and at their happiest. I do not believe seeing the corpse of a great dragon laying at my feet to be able to give me greater joy, then canceling a trade window from some grateful person.<br>
<br>
But to each their own lives and roles. I salute the courageous that stand before the greatest of dragons, but no more respectably than I salute that level 20 that risks all to help a friend. For that dragon slayer slays for his own glory, the young ranger seeks to give hope to a lost soul.<br>
<br>
Laleldil Tremulous 52 Vicar &lt;Order of the Green Knights&gt; (Raid Officer and Treasurer)<br>
Darlain Tenderfoot 25 Monk &lt;Order of the Green Knights&gt;<br>
Thollux Paells Server  <br>
